<div class="dablink">"Boltzmann" redirects here. For the lunar crater, see <a href="/wiki/Boltzmann_(crater)" title="Boltzmann (crater)">Boltzmann (crater)</a>.</div>
<p><b>Ludwig Eduard Boltzmann</b> (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1844-02-20"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="02-20"><a href="/wiki/February_20" title="February 20">February 20</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1844" title="1844">1844</a></span> – <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1906-09-05"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="09-05"><a href="/wiki/September_5" title="September 5">September 5</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1906" title="1906">1906</a></span>) was an <a href="/wiki/Austria" title="Austria">Austrian</a> <a href="/wiki/Physicist" title="Physicist">physicist</a> famous for his founding contributions in the fields of <a href="/wiki/Statistical_mechanics" title="Statistical mechanics">statistical mechanics</a> and <a href="/wiki/Statistical_thermodynamics" title="Statistical thermodynamics" class="mw-redirect">statistical thermodynamics</a>. He was one of the most important advocates for <a href="/wiki/Atomic_theory" title="Atomic theory">atomic theory</a> when that scientific model was still highly controversial.</p>
