<li><a href="/wiki/Philosophy_of_thermal_and_statistical_physics" title="Philosophy of thermal and statistical physics">Philosophy of thermal and statistical physics</a></li>
</ul>
<p><a name="References" id="References"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Ludwig_Boltzmann&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: References">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">References</span></h2>
<div class="references-small">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-springer-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-springer_0-0" title="">^</a></b> "Paul Ehrenfest (1880–1933) along with Nernst[,] Arrhenius, and Meitner must be considered among Boltzmann’s most outstanding students."—<cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFJ.C3.A4gerNablMeyer1999">Jäger, Gustav; Nabl, Josef; Meyer, Stephan (April 1999), "<a href="http://www.springerlink.com/content/vq5443477m7w7782/" class="external text" title="http://www.springerlink.com/content/vq5443477m7w7782/" rel="nofollow">Three Assistants on Boltzmann</a>", <i>Synthese</i>, <a href="http://www.springerlink.com/humanities-social-sciences-and-law/" class="external text" title="http://www.springerlink.com/humanities-social-sciences-and-law/" rel="nofollow">Humanities, Social Sciences and Law</a> (Springer Netherlands) <b>119</b> (1-2): 69–84, <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<span class="neverexpand"><a href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1023%2FA%3A1005239104047" class="external text" title="http://dx.doi.org/10.1023%2FA%3A1005239104047" rel="nofollow">10.1023/A:1005239104047</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Serial_Number" title="International Standard Serial Number">ISSN</a> <a href="http://worldcat.org/issn/1573-0964" class="external text" title="http://worldcat.org/issn/1573-0964" rel="nofollow">1573-0964</a><span class="printonly">, <a href="http://www.springerlink.com/content/vq5443477m7w7782/" class="external free" title="http://www.springerlink.com/content/vq5443477m7w7782/" rel="nofollow">http://www.springerlink.com/content/vq5443477m7w7782/</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">, retrieved on 2008-06-09</span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Three+Assistants+on+Boltzmann&amp;rft.jtitle=Synthese&amp;rft.aulast=J%C3%A4ger&amp;rft.aufirst=Gustav&amp;rft.au=J%C3%A4ger%2C+Gustav&amp;rft.au=Nabl%2